chapters.summary: The speaker apologized to Bernie for an unspecified incident involving moving vials of raccoon virus to the refrigerator.
chapters.title: Apologizing for the Incident

chapters.summary: The speaker explained that he was taking precautions after moving vials of raccoon virus to the refrigerator and advised Bernie to make two trips next time.
chapters.title: Explaining the Precautions

chapters.summary: The speaker was asked if he was okay and reassured the other person that he was probably fine and it was just a precaution in case there was a problem from moving the raccoon virus.
chapters.title: Reassuring He's Okay

chapters.summary: The speaker apologized for disrupting the date, explaining it was just a precaution and he'd be much sicker if there was really a problem from the raccoon virus incident.
chapters.title: Apologizing for Disrupting the Date

chapters.summary: The speaker apologized to Mr. Burdett for the disruption and told him not to worry as he had brought his date there.
chapters.title: Friends Arriving for the Date

chapters.summary: The speaker welcomed his friends inside and announced he had prepared something for them all.
chapters.title: Announcing the Song

chapters.summary: The speaker explained he wrote an anniversary song to celebrate the first date anniversary and then sang the song which humorously rhymed how lost he'd be without his girlfriend.
chapters.title: Singing the Anniversary Song

chapters.summary: After the song concluded, the friends expressed appreciation for the touching and amazing song.
chapters.title: Appreciating the Song
